      "I just want to preface this review by noting that I don't usually ever watch anything horror-related. The sole reason I watched this show was that Victoria Pedretti is in it, and I absolutely love her. Not that I know what I'm talking about, but she is such a skilled actor, and has killed every role she's done so far (you can also see her in The Haunting of Hill House, and You S2). I should also note that it was extremely hard to rate this based on the actual show, and not give it a 90-something because Victoria was in it. But at least I can try, right?\n\nThe Haunting of Bly Manor is the second installment of The Haunting anthology series, with The Haunting of Hill House coming before it. To start off, this show (and its predecessor) just kind of bums me out; there are some really sad moments in the show. I really appreciated the cinematography for this show, the camera work basically facilitated every good jump scare in the show. I'm not a big fan of jump scares, but I could see how well-done they were. Another thing the show did great was introducing mysteries early in the show that was resolved nicely later. I can explain what I mean by this with an example: early in the show we see a ghost of a plague-doctor, and it's not until the last couple of episodes that we find out why it's there in the first place. As with The Haunting of Hill House, this show's biggest strength lies in its ending, specifically the satisfaction the viewer feels once they finally understand everything that happened. This show is super confusing, and you basically spend the entire show trying to figure out what's happening, only to have everything revealed in the season finale.\n\nWhen making this show, Flanagan chose to bring on a few of the cast members from The Haunting of Hill House. I think he chose the best of the bunch to return for the next installment in this anthology (I mean if he chose to bring Victoria Pedretti back then obviously he took the best), so it's no wonder the cast of characters was so great.\n\nSo yeah, to sum this show up, it had a great season finale, a great mechanism for revealing the entire ghost story, and obviously a great set of actors playing great roles. I can only rate a horror show so high; it's just not one of my favorite genres. Also, I think the show took a little while to get rolling, as the back-half of the show was much better than the front-half. @ me in the comments if you agreed or thought differently, or have any additional thoughts. Thanks for reading!",
