      "So we're finally underway with The Falcon and The Winter Soldier! Right off the bat, I think I'm going to like this one more than WandaVision. Obviously, the first episode was mostly exposition, which is why this is getting a lower rating since I really enjoy the intense action (which we got at the beginning of this episode). This episode had 3 main things going on. 1. the rise of a new anarchist group that wants the world to go back to the state during the 5-year blip period, named the Flag-Smashers. 2. Sam Wilson's family relations and financial issues. 3. Bucky adapting to being a normal 106-year-old civilian. During this first episode, Sam and Bucky actually don't ever end up meeting at all. I assume we're going to see a team-up soon, with the goal being to take down the Flag-Smashers, whose leader appears to be strength-enhanced in some way. We're also introduced to a new character, Torres, who is a member of the Army, but teams up with Sam at the beginning of the episode.\n\nThe one thing that's still up in the air is whether or not Steve Rogers is dead or not. We don't get an explicit answer from Sam Wilson, so I'm hoping this will be revealed down the line in a later episode. It was also really interesting seeing Bucky in the modern-world attempting to be normal, I doubt this will last long but it was fun to see. Another awesome thing that happened was a short appearance from Rhodey at the beginning of the episode. I hope he comes back for some more episodes.\n\nSo yeah, those are my thoughts on episode 1! I'm expecting this one to ramp up much faster than WandaVision, so I'd bet we're in for some good action in the next few episodes. @ me in the comments with your thoughts! Stay tuned for more The Falcon and The Winter Soldier reviews coming on Saturday mornings!",
