      "I know exactly what you're thinking: this is a sequel, so why are you reviewing it before its predecessor?? It's because I had never watched this movie until yesterday, so I want to review it while I'm fresh off seeing it, which is why I'm reviewing this before Patriot Games. So rolling right into it, this is a super typical Harrison Ford action movie, so you're getting exactly what you're expecting if you've seen some other things like Patriot Games, The Fugitive, or Air Force One. Whereas Patriot Games, the predecessor of Clear and Present Danger involves Jack Ryan protecting his family from an Irish terrorist group out for revenge, Clear and Present Danger focuses much more on the national level, and on the wrongdoings of the US government in relation to the Colombian drug cartels.\n\nTo give a super quick overview summary, Jack Ryan becomes the acting Director of the CIA when his dear friend and mentor Admiral Greer is diagnosed with terminal cancer. When an American businessman and friend of the President is murdered by a Colombian cartel, a secret off-the-books strike team is sent to Colombia to kill the heads of the drug cartels in revenge. However, things aren't that simple, as Jack Ryan starts to discover ties between the businessman and the cartels, so he starts trying to uncover what's really happening. To make matters more confusing for Ryan, one of the cartel's intelligence officers is attempting to overthrow the head of the cartel, leading to more secret deals and back-stabbings.\n\nThe thing I really liked about this movie was how the viewer was discovering and finding out new facts along with Ryan, which is genius because it makes the plot much more interesting since we feel like we're in his shoes and can relate to all of his thoughts and feelings. This element of mystery of not knowing what's next made for a very interesting film for me. I think that's one of the biggest differences between Clear and Present Danger and Patriot Games since Patriot Games don't really have the same mysterious aspect. With that being said, I do prefer Patriot Games simply because I think the intensity is higher than Clear and Present Danger since the story is filled with more passion and anger given that it revolves around a personal vendetta. Other than that, there's nothing super unique or special about this movie: it's simply a solid action movie that I enjoyed watching.\n\nSo yeah, those are my thoughts on the second Harrison Ford Jack Ryan movie. Make sure to leave your own thoughts down below!",
