    content:
      "After a 14-month-long postponement, Black Widow finally hit the theaters! Not going to lie, this movie was exactly what I expected it to be from the trailers: a pure action movie (with no superhero tricks or gimmicks) focusing on unraveling the mystery behind Natasha Romanoff's past. There's nothing super special about this movie, but it delivers the same consistent quality that Marvel has been producing for years. In terms of other Marvel movies, it's definitely middle of the pack. It wasn't anything extraordinary, but it definitely was a high-quality movie that made for an excellent theater-going experience for me. I'm not going to reveal anything about the plot of this movie, especially since this is my first review on a movie's opening weekend!\n\nWhat I will share are some things that I found really cool, that can be seen or reasonably inferred from the many trailers released around this film. 1. Taskmaster was finally introduced into the MCU! My knowledge on Taskmaster is pretty limited to some of the animated Marvel TV shows from the 2000s, but I was happy to see the similarities, specifically the fighting technique copying ability. 2. This film is set in 2016 (think right after the conclusion of Captain America: Civil War). Clearly the movie was set in the past after Natasha's fate in Avengers: Endgame, but this answers the question of exactly when it takes place. 3. The post-credits scene contained the first massive link to a Disney+ show, specifically The Falcon and The Winter Soldier. This is a really interesting and sneaky marketing tactic to push Disney+ onto the audience.\n\nLet's talk about new characters! Almost every single character in this film was new, so I just wanna highlight my favorites. The two main supporting characters, Yelena and (Alexei aka Red Guardian) were definitely my favorite characters in the entire film. From the trailer, I already knew Red Guardian was going to be really funny, and he definitely lived up to it, delivering a lot of laughs in an otherwise super serious movie. What I didn't see coming from the trailer was how hilarious Yelena was. She was without a doubt my favorite character from the movie, specifically one of my favorite lines came when she started mocking Natasha's fighting poses.\n\nSo yeah, those are my thoughts on this new release! I hope everyone who goes to see it enjoys being back in the theaters for a Marvel Movie. Hopefully, someday I'll get around to finishing those other Marvel Reviews when I have the time. Leave any comments down below with any questions or thoughts!",
